Jul 5 2006	Better than expected Loved the Shuttle Good Value	I got this hotel through Priceline for an excellent price, given that I was there for a holiday weekend. At first I had some misgivings about location and the ease with which I would be able to get dowtown for inside the loop activities. Luckily, it was much easier than I had expected.The hotel is about .5 miles from the Racine Blue Line stop, so it's not too bad of a walk. If you are not a walker, there is a hotel shuttle bus that will take you to and from the train station for free. The shuttle takes hotel guests within a 1 mile radius of the hotel, so it won't take you all the way downtown, but will take you to the train station, restaurants (Giordano's was great!), Little Italy, Greektown, the hospitals, Harpo studios, etc., all of which are within 1 mile. I had no car and a CTA train pass and things worked out very well. Whenever we called the shuttle for a pick up, it never took more than 10-15 minutes, and the shuttle drivers were very helpful and full of suggestions for tourists. The hotel itself was nice, typical Marriott quality. The front desk staff were curteous and helpful. We had a non-smoking room, but it smelled a bit of old smoke, so that was a minus. The room was large and the amenities were good (Bath &amp; Body Works toiletries, cofee/tea in room, good tv channel selection, excellent bed/linens). Another bonus is there is free internet access in the lobby and in the business center for guests. All in all, I was pleasantly surprised. I would certainly consider staying here again. Not the best hotel if you want to be right in the heart of the loop and near all the attractions, but well worth it for the price. A nice respite from the downtown hustle and bustle, but still close enough to be convenient.	
